Chełm () is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Lidzbark Warmiński, within Lidzbark County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  south-west of Lidzbark Warmiński and  north of the regional capital Olsztyn. It is located in the historic region of Warmia.
